0. Definitions
The following terms are defined in this license:

- "Server Union" (Abbreviation: SU): Refers to the server union within the Discord Japan community.

- "SAUMDA" (Abbreviation: SUMDA): The name of this software.

- "SUMDA Account": Refers to user information (personal information including the password required for system login) registered in the database (hereinafter "DB").

- "User": An operating member within the SU organization, or an SU member who can access the software information.

- "Administrator": A person with administrative privileges on the DB, or a person granted administrative privileges through a SUMDA account.

- "DB": Refers to the database.

1. Permission Conditions
This software is permitted for use only under the following conditions:

- Usable only within the SU organization.

2. Usage Restrictions
The following persons are not permitted to use this software under any circumstances. - Discord users outside the SU organization.
- Non-Discord users.
- Individuals without DB operation privileges.

If any of the above restricted individuals use this software, it will be considered a data breach and they will be held legally responsible.

